   "source": [
    "# Using Claude via Amazon Bedrock: Drug Synergy Prediction\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook mirrors the ChatGPT API notebook but uses **Claude on Amazon Bedrock** instead of OpenAI.\n",
    "\n"
    "- Make sure `boto3` is installed\n",
    "- Ensure your account has Bedrock model access enabled for Claude"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Section 1: Install Dependencies and Load Dataset**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install boto3 pandas numpy scikit-learn tqdm"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import boto3\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import time\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from tqdm import tqdm\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score, average_precision_score\n",
    "from torch.utils.data import Dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Initialize the Bedrock client. This uses your local AWS credentials (from `ada credentials update`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "bedrock = boto3.client('bedrock-runtime', region_name='us-east-1')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Helper function to call Claude via Bedrock"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def call_claude(messages, system=None, model_id='us.anthropic.claude-sonnet-4-6', max_tokens=1024):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Call Claude via Bedrock. messages is a list of {role, content} dicts.\"\"\"\n",
    "    body = {\n",
    "        'anthropic_version': 'bedrock-2023-05-31',\n",
    "        'messages': messages,\n",
    "        'max_tokens': max_tokens\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    if system:\n",
    "        body['system'] = system\n",
    "    \n",
    "    response = bedrock.invoke_model(\n",
    "        modelId=model_id,\n",
    "        body=json.dumps(body)\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    result = json.loads(response['body'].read())\n",
    "    return result['content'][0]['text']\n"
   ]
  },
