      "Based on the information provided, the drug combination of AZD4877 and AZD1208 in the T24 cell line was actually determined to be **negative** (synergy < 5), not synergistic. Here are some details to explain this:\n",
      "\n",
      "## Why the Combination is NOT Synergistic:\n",
      "\n",
      "### Drug Profiles:\n",
      "- **AZD4877** (Eg5/KIF11 inhibitor): Shows **very high sensitivity** (99.091 relative inhibition), meaning it is already extremely effective on its own in the T24 cell line.\n",
      "- **AZD1208** (PIM kinase inhibitor): Shows **very low sensitivity** (3.803 relative inhibition), meaning it has minimal effect on its own in this cell line.\n",
      "\n",
      "### Reasons for Lack of Synergy:\n",
      "1. **Ceiling Effect**: AZD4877 already achieves near-complete inhibition (~99%), leaving little room for additional benefit from AZD1208.\n",
      "2. **Limited Activity of AZD1208**: With only ~3.8% relative inhibition, AZD1208 has minimal biological activity in T24 cells, contributing little to the combination.\n",
      "3. **Different Pathways**: The mitotic inhibition (AZD4877) and PIM kinase inhibition (AZD1208) pathways may not have meaningful cross-talk in this particular cell line.\n",
      "4. **Cell Line Context**: T24 is a bladder cancer cell line, and PIM kinase signaling may not be a critical survival pathway here.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
